# Privacy Policy – Church Admin App

**Effective Date:** May 6, 2025  
**Developer:** Eregion Codeworks

Church Admin is a mobile app designed to help a small group manage attendance and meetings for their local church. This privacy policy outlines how the app handles user data.

## 1. Data Collection
The Church Admin app:
- Collects anonymous attendance data (number of attendees in various categories)
- Stores data securely in Google’s Firebase Cloud Firestore
- Does not collect names, emails, or personal identifiers

## 2. Authentication
- The app uses anonymous sign-in via Firebase Authentication
- No personal information is required to use the app

## 3. Data Storage & Use
- All data is stored in Firebase Firestore and is only accessible to authorized users of the app
- Data is used only for attendance tracking and reporting within your church organization

## 4. Data Sharing
We do not share, sell, or transmit your data to any third parties. The app is intended for private organizational use only.

## 5. Third-Party Services
This app uses:
- [Firebase Authentication](https://firebase.google.com/products/auth)
- [Cloud Firestore](https://firebase.google.com/products/firestore)

These services may collect technical data such as device type and OS version for security and stability purposes.

## 6. User Rights
Users who wish to request deletion of any records or data may contact the administrator of the app or the developer listed below.

## Contact
If you have any questions or concerns, contact:  
[you@example.com]
